<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN251-kilavi">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai: vākai; tuṟai: tāpatavākai ...māṟpittiyār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"></p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN251">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>ōvat taṉṉa viṭaṉuṭai varaippiṟ</l>
<l>pāvai yaṉṉa kuṟuntoṭi makaḷi</l>
<l>riḻainilai nekiḻtta maḷḷaṟ kaṇṭikuṅ</l>
<l>kaḻaikka ṇeṭuvarai yaruvi yāṭik</l>
<l>kāṉa yāṉai tanta viṟakiṟ</l>
<l>kaṭunteṟaṟ centī vēṭṭup</l>
<l>puṟantāḻ puricaṭai pularttu vōṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l> Let us see the warrior who made loose from [their] positions the jewels (3)</l>
<l>  of women with little bangles who are like dolls, (2)</l>
<l>  in houses of vast perimeter, like pictures, (1)</l>
<l>  – the one who [now] dries [his] matted hair in strands that hang down on [his] back, (7)</l>
<l>  sacrificing in fierce, scorching, hot fires (6)</l>
<l>  from fuel brought by a forest elephant, (5)</l>
<l>  bathing in a waterfall on the large mountain with spots of bamboo. (4)</l>   
</lg>
    </div>
